To find (A x B) ∪ (A x B x B), we first need to find the Cartesian products A x B and A x B x B.

A x B = {(1, x), (1, y), (2, x), (2, y), (3, x), (3, y)}

A x B x B = {(1, x, x), (1, x, y), (1, y, x), (1, y, y), (2, x, x), (2, x, y), (2, y, x), (2, y, y), (3, x, x), (3, x, y), (3, y, x), (3, y, y)}

Now, we find the union of these two sets:

(A x B) ∪ (A x B x B) = {(1, x), (1, y), (2, x), (2, y), (3, x), (3, y), (1, x, x), (1, x, y), (1, y, x), (1, y, y), (2, x, x), (2, x, y), (2, y, x), (2, y, y), (3, x, x), (3, x, y), (3, y, x), (3, y, y)}
